  "text": "## Envoy Access Logging Infrastructure Audit\n\n### Access Log Sinks (Implementations)\n\nThe following access logger sink implementations are defined in Envoy v1.31.2:\n\n#### 1. File Logger\n- **Repo**: github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n- **Implementation**: source/extensions/access_loggers/file/config.cc, source/extensions/access_loggers/common/file_access_log_impl.h\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/file/v3/file.proto (data-plane-api--84e84367)\n- **JSON Support**: YES - Supports structured (JSON) logging via three formats:\n  - `format`: Text format (deprecated, plain text only)\n  - `json_format`: Deprecated JSON format with all values rendered as strings\n  - `typed_json_format`: Deprecated JSON format with typed values (strings, numbers, booleans)\n  - `log_format`: Primary modern format using SubstitutionFormatString, which supports both text and JSON\n\n#### 2. Fluentd Logger\n- **Repo**: github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n- **Implementation**: source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/config.cc, source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/fluentd_access_log_impl.h\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/v3/fluentd.proto (data-plane-api--84e84367)\n- **JSON Support**: YES - Structured (JSON) logging via intermediate JSON formatter\n  - Uses `createJsonFormatter()` to generate JSON structure with typed values (strings, numbers, booleans)\n  - Converts JSON payload to MessagePack protocol for transmission to Fluentd\n\n#### 3. gRPC Access Log Service (HTTP)\n- **Repo**: github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n- **Implementation**: source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_grpc_access_log_impl.h, source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_config.cc\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto (data-plane-api--84e84367)\n- **JSON Support**: NO - Unstructured binary format only\n  - Uses Protocol Buffer binary format (HTTPAccessLogEntry and TCPAccessLogEntry proto messages)\n  - Transmits data as binary protobuf messages, not human-readable JSON\n\n#### 4. gRPC Access Log Service (TCP)\n- **Repo**: github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n- **Implementation**: source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_grpc_access_log_impl.h, source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_config.cc\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto (data-plane-api--84e84367)\n- **JSON Support**: NO - Unstructured binary format only\n  - Uses Protocol Buffer binary format (same as HTTP variant)\n\n#### 5. Stream Logger (stdout/stderr)\n- **Repo**: github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n- **Implementation**: source/extensions/access_loggers/stream/config.cc, source/extensions/access_loggers/common/stream_access_log_common_impl.h\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto (data-plane-api--84e84367)\n- **JSON Support**: YES - Configurable structured (JSON) logging\n  - Uses SubstitutionFormatString which supports both text format and JSON format\n  - Configuration determines whether output is plain text or JSON\n\n#### 6. OpenTelemetry Logger\n- **Repo**: github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n- **Implementation**: source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/config.cc, source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/access_log_impl.h, source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/substitution_formatter.h\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto (data-plane-api--84e84367)\n- **JSON Support**: YES - Structured OpenTelemetry format\n  - Uses OpenTelemetry proto format with structured attributes (KeyValueList)\n  - Supports nested JSON objects via OpenTelemetry's structured type system\n  - Allows configuration of body and attributes as structured data\n\n#### 7. Wasm Logger\n- **Repo**: github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n- **Implementation**: source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/config.cc, source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/wasm_access_log_impl.h\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto (data-plane-api--84e84367)\n- **JSON Support**: IMPLEMENTATION-DEPENDENT\n  - Custom WASM-based implementation with pluggable format\n  - Format determined by specific WASM module implementation\n\n### Access Log Filters (Not Sinks)\n\nThe following access log filters are defined but are not sinks; they determine whether logs should be emitted:\n\n#### 1. CEL Expression Filter\n- **Repo**: github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n- **Implementation**: source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/config.cc, source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/cel.h\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto (data-plane-api--84e84367)\n- **Purpose**: Evaluates CEL (Common Expression Language) expressions to filter which logs are emitted\n- **JSON Support**: N/A (This is a filter, not a sink)\n\n### Proto-Only Definitions (Not Implemented)\n\nThe following proto definitions exist in data-plane-api--84e84367 but do not have corresponding C++ implementations in Envoy v1.31.2:\n\n#### 1. Stats Logger\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stats/v3/stats.proto\n- **Status**: Proto definition only, no C++ implementation\n- **Purpose**: Would emit custom Envoy stats based on access logs\n\n#### 2. Dynamic Modules Logger\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto\n- **Status**: Proto definition only, no C++ implementation\n- **Purpose**: Would allow loading custom logging implementations via dlopen\n\n#### 3. Process Rate Limit Filter\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto\n- **Status**: Proto definition only, appears to be for future implementation\n- **Purpose**: Filter for rate limiting access log emission\n\n### Summary\n\n**Loggers Supporting Structured (JSON) Logging**:\n1. File Logger - YES\n2. Fluentd Logger - YES (JSON intermediate format)\n3. Stream Logger - YES (when configured for JSON)\n4. OpenTelemetry Logger - YES\n5. Wasm Logger - IMPLEMENTATION-DEPENDENT\n\n**Loggers Supporting Only Unstructured (Binary) Format**:\n1. gRPC Access Log Service (HTTP) - Protobuf binary only\n2. gRPC Access Log Service (TCP) - Protobuf binary only\n\n**Filters (Not Sinks)**:\n1. CEL Expression Filter - Used to determine if logs are emitted"
}

